23/01/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Croatian Chief State Prosecutor Mladen Bajic and his BiH counterpart, Marinko Jurcevic, signed a protocol of co-operation Friday (21 January) regarding the fight against all forms of serious crime, including war crimes. The document calls for increased information exchanges and direct communication between prosecutors' offices in the two countries, with the aim of preventing criminals from escaping across the border. (HINA, FENA - 21/01/05)
